A7736 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZ     05-23 0315
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOP PICK RECOVERING WELL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Three weeks after suffering an injured left shoulder at
minicamp, top draft pick  &UR; David Boston is making a speedy recovery.
</P>
<P>
   Wide receivers coach  &UR; Vic Rapp said he spoke to Boston on Friday
and the Ohio State product told him he was ``healing well.''
</P>
<P>
   Boston suffered a fractured bone in his left shoulder in a
collision with cornerback  &UR; Corey Chavous.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's back in Columbus (Ohio),'' Rapp said. ``The doctors who
are treating him there told him the (bone) calcified real
quickly.''
</P>
<P>
   Boston's brother,  &UR; Byron, a Dallas policeman, said Saturday that
Boston is feeling much better and should be 100 percent for the
July 30 start of training camp.
</P>
<P>
   Boston will return to Valley on June 12, five days after rookie
camp begins.
</P>
<P>
   Rapp said that as a precautionary measure, Boston won't
participate in any drills at rookie camp. &QL; 
Temporary loss?
</P>
<P>
   Coach  &UR; Vince Tobin doesn't think the team's future in the Valley
was sealed by last Tuesday's defeat of the Rio Salado Crossing
convention center and stadium project.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is just the first salvo,'' Tobin said.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback  &UR; Jake Plummer thinks the players can get beyond the
loss at the ballot box.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've still got to go on,'' Plummer said. ``We have a season
to play.'' &QL; 
Not cooling off &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Second-year pro  &UR; Andy McCullough, who entered Saturday as the
NFL Europe League's receiving-yards leader, had three touchdown
catches in Frankfurt's 42-35 loss to the Scottish Claymores.
</P>
<P>
   McCullough's three scores tied a league record, and he now has a
league-high seven touchdowns for the season. &QL; 
Contract update &QL; 
The one-year tender contracts signed by offensive linemen
 &UR; Aaron &UR; Graham and  &UR; James Dexter on Friday are worth $429,000 each.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
