Committee on Monday weighs whether the president's salary should be
raised from $200,000 a year, a level where it has remained for
decades. Proposal would double president's salary to $400,000 the
day President Clinton leaves office. Such a move would likely lead
to higher pay throughout the federal government.. (Malone, Cox News
Service). 25.
