r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-WALKMAN-ANNIVERSARY25     05-23 0329
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WALKMAN-ANNIVERSARY25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MiniDisk unit makes digital recordings
 &HT;    
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cos News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   In 1979 Iranian students stormed the U.S. Embassy in Tehran,
taking the occupants hostage, Anwar el-Sadat and Menachim Begin
signed a treaty ending a 30-year war between Egypt and Israel, and
a reactor accident at the Three Mile Island generating station
spewed nuclear waste into the air.
</P>
<P>
   In the face of all that, it's not surprising if you've forgotten
another milestone from 1979: Sony introduced the ``Soundabout,''
later to be known as the Sony Walkman personal stereo.
</P>
<P>
   Sony said critics at first were skeptical of the idea of a small
stereo cassette player that played its music through headsets
rather than through speakers.
</P>
<P>
   But the Walkman was an immediate success in Japan and about
50,000 of them sold in the first two months.
</P>
<P>
   One of the latest additions to the Walkman line is the MZ-R55
portable MiniDisc recorder/player.
</P>
<P>
   The MZ-R55 records and plays music on Sony MiniDiscs, which are
small discs that store digital recordings similar to those found on
compact discs. But while almost all compact discs are prerecorded,
most MiniDiscs are sold blank for consumers to make their own
recordings.
</P>
<P>
   A 74-minute MiniDisc sells for about $4.49 when purchased
singly, according to Sony. They're less expensive purchased in
packs of three or more.
</P>
<P>
   The MZ-R55 is the world's smallest MiniDisc recorder/player at 3
1/8 inches tall, 3 3/8 inches wide and less than an inch thick.
It's powered by a rechargeable nickel metal hydride battery.
</P>
<P>
   The player has digital connecting cables to tie into home stereo
systems to record the owner's favorite music. It allows the user to
attach titles, dates and times to recordings, and the titles show
up on the unit's LCD screen.
</P>
<P>
   The suggested retail price is $349.95.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-23-99 1605EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
