<P>
   VIOLENCE-TURNER _ DENVER _ Maybe it's time to find a new
nickname for Ted Turner. ''Captain Outrageous'' actually was
something closer to courageous here Saturday night, refusing to
follow the example of so many others in the entertainment and media
business by dodging questions about the recent spate of school
shootings. In fact, Turner brought up the subject himself in
accepting the Denver Press Club's fifth annual Damon Runyon Award.
Turner said, CNN and Time Magazine asked 500 teenagers about
possible causes. While availability of guns ranked No. 1, the
amount of violence in television, movies, music and the news
followed close behind. ''I've got to feel partly responsible for
that,'' said Turner, the founder of CNN and now vice chairman of
the Time Warner multimedia empire. (Vejnoska, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
