<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, May 24, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEES-SOCAL (Los Angeles) _ Refugees from war-torn Kosovo,
spending their first weekend with host families in Southern
California, went to the beach, movie houses, fast-food restaurants
and tourist sites. By Phillip W. Brown and Robert Monroe. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   STAR-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ The Force continues to deliver
mixed signals by dominating business at the nation's multiplexes,
but falling well short of sky-high expectations. ``Star Wars
Episode 1: The Phantom Menace'' obliterated the competition with an
estimated $61.8 million at 2,970 theaters during Friday-Sunday,
pushing its five-day total to $103.6 million, studio sources said
Sunday. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-LIGHTNING (Los Angeles) _ A freak storm hit the Los Angeles
area overnight, bringing intense thunder and lightning to some
areas, including the Angeles National Forest-area where a ranger
was struck by lightning in his back yard. By Michael Coit. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RACING-PIDGEONS (Los Angeles) _ Flying nearly 60 mph over
hundreds of miles, Rusty Hemsath's racing pigeons dodge hawks,
power lines and storms with a single goal _ getting home. By
Michael Coit. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-SCHOOLS (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles school officials have
failed to comply with a 14-month-old state requirement that
security grilles on portable classrooms have latches that would let
children escape in a fire. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
