KINSHASA, Congo: recognized yet.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Etienne Tshisekedi, the country's most popular opposition
leader, has declined to attend the debate unless he and others have
a say in its organization, said his political adviser, Jean-Joseph
Mukendi.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Jean-Baptiste Sondji, a longtime opponent of Mobutu who
served as Kabila's Minister of Health until he was fired for
criticizing the government last fall, said that Kabila would have
to make sweeping changes to his government if it hopes to survive.
Hard-liners, characterized by ``inexperience and incompetence,''
have surrounded Kabila and are stopping him from reaching out to
opponents, Sondji said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everything is not lost on the condition that he draws the
lessons of his failures,'' he said. ``And if corrects them, nothing
is lost. But it will take a lot of courage, because he will really
have to commit hara kiri regarding what has happened in the last
two years.''
</P>
</TEXT>
