<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Monday,
May 24. If you have any questions, please call The Star's News Desk
at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   THRIFT-EXEC-THREETAKES (SPRINGFIELD, Mo.) _ One of the untold
stories of the savings and loan debacle will come to a close Monday
when prison doors open and a graying 56-year-old man walks out,
free at last. His name is Ed Morris. He was sentenced to 46 months
in prison for encouraging the public to invest in his St.
Louis-area S&AMP;L that later went kerplunk. Morris says he is
innocent. Lots of former S&AMP;L executives _ including Morris _ are
convinced that Congress lost its collective mind a decade ago and
unleashed a reign of terror on the S&AMP;L industry. By CHARLES R.T.
CRUMPLEY. Story will move in the ``a'' cetegory. &QL;
</P>
