   SAUDI-SUCCESSION (Riyadh, Saudi Arabia) _ The king of Saudi
Arabia, long ailing, is 78. His designated successor, the crown
prince, is 76. The defense minister, seen as next in line for the
throne, is 75. At a time when leaderships are changing and passing
to a younger generation elsewhere in the Middle East, the prospect
of a continuing gerontocracy is beginning to provoke open concern
among businessmen, politicians and even members of the royal family
and Saudi Arabia's allies. By Douglas Jehl.
</P>
